        "faq-1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does a probiotic help with joint pain?",
            "answer": "<p>Chronic joint inflammation is often driven by bacterial endotoxins (LPS) leaking through a compromised gut barrier into your bloodstream. Your immune system treats these as threats, triggering systemic inflammatory cascades — CRP, IL-6, TNF-alpha — that concentrate in synovial tissue. Origin's strains restore the gut barrier integrity that stops this leakage at the source. When LPS stops entering circulation, the downstream inflammatory load on your joints drops.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long before I notice a difference in joint stiffness?",
            "answer": "<p>Most people notice a reduction in morning stiffness within 2-4 weeks. Full results — including reduced exercise recovery time and lower overall inflammation — typically appear within 6-8 weeks as the gut barrier strengthens and bacterial populations stabilize. Microbiome restoration is a progressive process, not an overnight fix.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I take Origin alongside glucosamine or turmeric?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes. Origin addresses the upstream cause — gut barrier permeability and systemic endotoxemia — while supplements like glucosamine address cartilage and turmeric dampens inflammatory signals. They work through different mechanisms. Many customers start with both, then reduce or eliminate the downstream supplements as the gut barrier recovers and their inflammation baseline drops.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Why does joint pain get worse under Western environmental stress or dietary change?",
            "answer": "<p>The HELIUS study (2,084 subjects, 6 population groups) demonstrated that biology determines microbiome composition more than diet, age, or medical history. When you adopt a Western diet, the specific bacterial populations that produce tight-junction proteins — the compounds that seal your gut barrier — deplete within one generation. That barrier breach is the mechanism behind the inflammatory conditions that emerge years under environmental stress, including joint inflammation that didn't exist in your parents at your age.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq-5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "What makes Origin different from other probiotics for inflammation?",
            "answer": "<p>Most probiotics use generic strains selected for a hypothetical average person. Origin's four strains — L. acidophilus, B. lactis, L. plantarum, and L. paracasei — are specifically chosen for their documented roles in gut barrier maintenance and anti-inflammatory cytokine reduction. MAKTREK Bi-Pass delivery ensures they survive stomach acid and arrive in your gut alive. Dead bacteria can't seal anything. FOS prebiotic feeds them on arrival so they colonize rather than pass through.</p>"
          }
        }
